00:45:11,472 --> 00:45:12,713
It tends to be set up such that

1030
00:45:13,894 --> 00:45:16,337
to a small number of winners, all of the rewards go.

1031
00:45:17,558 --> 00:45:19,280
That means that in such an environment,

1032
00:45:19,360 --> 00:45:21,682
a typical result, the 50th percentile,

1033
00:45:21,762 --> 00:45:24,945
is actually either failure or a struggle.

1034
00:45:25,626 --> 00:45:26,747
It's not a success to be typical.

1035
00:45:28,852 --> 00:45:32,434
And if you use typical strategies, you should expect typical results.

1036
00:45:33,214 --> 00:45:38,116
So, from this logic, the only option is to use an atypical, high-variance strategy.

1037
00:45:39,817 --> 00:45:44,980
And these will be strategies, by definition, that most people are not using or likely won't

1038
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:45,340
agree with.

1039
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:49,602
Because if a lot of people are using them, then you're back to the typical results.

1040
00:45:51,011 --> 00:45:52,572
But take heart, one rule of history is that

1041
00:45:52,592 --> 00:45:54,473
the social milieu is always making mistakes.

1042
00:45:54,933 --> 00:45:56,614
It's true in every society and all time everywhere.

1043
00:45:56,674 --> 00:45:58,815
So just because nobody's thinking a certain way

1044
00:45:58,875 --> 00:46:01,037
or asking certain questions doesn't mean that they're dumb.

1045
00:46:02,958 --> 00:46:05,259
In a tournament market, where the average results

1046
00:46:05,439 --> 00:46:07,440
equal failure, I don't think you should be frightened

1047
00:46:07,480 --> 00:46:10,382
of following individual logic to a different conclusion

1048
00:46:10,582 --> 00:46:12,263
or frightened of taking a strange frame.

1049
00:46:13,384 --> 00:46:16,065
I think it should be more frightening to follow the group.

1050
00:46:17,646 --> 00:46:18,327
Thank you very much.

