one thing that the audience can do is abdicate responsibility for what's happening on screen.

1068
00:47:19,447 --> 00:47:22,949
We feel empathy, but that's probably the only way we can actually survive watching Game

1069
00:47:23,009 --> 00:47:25,670
of Thrones because, well, at least that wasn't our fault.

1070
00:47:26,310 --> 00:47:27,892
versus when you're doing something in a game,

1071
00:47:28,532 --> 00:47:30,334
people feel implicated in the success

1072
00:47:30,814 --> 00:47:31,975
of what's happening on screen.

1073
00:47:32,476 --> 00:47:34,217
I'm wondering how you're drawing the line

1074
00:47:34,297 --> 00:47:35,819
on the one hand where people actually form

1075
00:47:35,859 --> 00:47:37,420
this emotional connection,

1076
00:47:37,540 --> 00:47:39,042
but also feel they're responsible

1077
00:47:39,082 --> 00:47:40,243
for what's going on screen,

1078
00:47:40,983 --> 00:47:42,204
but you're telling them,

1079
00:47:42,845 --> 00:47:44,747
yeah, but it's not a fair game, right?

1080
00:47:44,787 --> 00:47:46,789
Like, the fact that you can be competent

1081
00:47:47,589 --> 00:47:48,610
is not really important.

1082
00:47:48,910 --> 00:47:50,292
I think there's a balance of influence.

1083
00:47:51,052 --> 00:47:53,194
that at least this is the strategy that RimWorld took.

1084
00:47:53,314 --> 00:47:54,494
The player can influence the game,

1085
00:47:55,015 --> 00:47:56,395
but they don't control every single thing

1086
00:47:56,455 --> 00:47:57,676
that their characters do.

1087
00:47:58,417 --> 00:48:01,198
They lay out priorities or set a schedule,

1088
00:48:01,839 --> 00:48:04,000
but the colonists that you're controlling

1089
00:48:04,040 --> 00:48:05,421
won't always follow what you want them to do.

1090
00:48:05,961 --> 00:48:08,162
