1091
00:48:08,182 --> 00:48:10,064
they might go crazy, or they might just fall asleep,

1092
00:48:10,084 --> 00:48:11,284
or so on and so forth.

1093
00:48:11,324 --> 00:48:13,405
So I think in a game where you control people directly,

1094
00:48:13,626 --> 00:48:16,747
or control a protagonist at every moment and every action,

1095
00:48:17,950 --> 00:48:19,331
A lot of this would have to be reinterpreted

1096
00:48:19,771 --> 00:48:21,212
because you wouldn't be able to abdicate anything.

1097
00:48:21,232 --> 00:48:23,374
It wouldn't be the feeling of watching something.

1098
00:48:23,794 --> 00:48:25,876
But in BrimWorld, you're far enough away

1099
00:48:25,896 --> 00:48:26,577
from what's going on

1100
00:48:27,097 --> 00:48:28,358
and the moment-to-moment interactions

1101
00:48:28,778 --> 00:48:31,080
that even though you influence the context of the situation

1102
00:48:31,100 --> 00:48:33,842
and set the overall priorities of some of the characters,

1103
00:48:36,124 --> 00:48:38,246
you are not exactly in control.

1104
00:48:38,306 --> 00:48:40,228
And so you can get into the mental frame of watching it

1105
00:48:40,588 --> 00:48:41,749
and saying, this thing happened,

1106
00:48:41,789 --> 00:48:43,470
not I did this thing necessarily.

1107
00:48:43,490 --> 00:48:44,731
Does that make sense?

1108
00:48:44,951 --> 00:48:45,492
Yeah, of course.

1109
00:48:45,712 --> 00:48:45,872
Thanks.

1110
00:48:46,212 --> 00:48:46,432
All right.

